"@HJSDGCE":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/53b25bdf6368722518550400#post_53b25bdf6368722518550400
They don't use many spices. But they have plentiful other flavourings. I find Japanese foods to be pretty similar to Scandinavian foods. Both utilize much seafood, serve things cold, and hot soups. Korean cuisine uses a lot of garlic, pickles, *ginseng*, Spam, and forage crops such as wild garlic, perilla leaves, mushrooms, and acorns.
